ARTICLE2 TERM, REGULA TORY APPROVALS AND TERMINATION 2.1 Commencement and Duration The Coordinated Operating Agreement became effective as of August 25, 2008, and shall remain in full force and effect through the Effective Date of this Amended and Restated Coordinated Operating Agreement. This Amended Restated Coordinated Operating Agreement shall remain in effect until terminated in accordance with the provisions of Article 2 of this Agreement. This Agreement will remain in effect as long as there is at least one (1) valid interconnection agreement for operating either the Glacier Wind l Project or the Glacier Wind 2 Project with NorthWestern or Glacier Electric; provided, however, that the Parties may mutually terminate this Agreement at anytime. 2.2 Regulatory Approvals (a) The Parties shall file this Agreement with FERC and request a regulatory effective date no later than July 1, 2009, in order to carry out their obligations hereunder, and each Party shall comply with and maintain any necessary Regulatory Approvals and co-operate with the other Parties in obtaining, complying with and maintaining such Regulatory Approvals. (b) Notwithstanding execution by the Parties, this Amended and Restated Coordinated Operating Agreement shall not become effective until the Effective Date as defined in this Agreement. 2.3 Termination- Cessation of Operations This Agreement may be terminated by either Party by giving the other Party written notice thereof at any time after all the generating facilities within the OW A Balancing Authority Area have been removed from service by reason of the permanent cessation of all commercial operations of such facilities such that no Points of Interconnection remain. 2.4 Termination- Bankruptcy If either Pany should: (a) take the benefit of any statute now or hereafter in force, for bankrupt or insolvent debtors (including, without limitation, the applicable articles of the United States Bankruptcy Code or similar legislation)~ (b) have an order made or a resolution passed for the winding up or other termination of the existence of such Party; or (c) have a liquidator, receiver or receiver manager of the business or undertaking of such Party duly appointed; then the Party not subject to any of the events described in subsections (a)-(c) of this Section 2.4 may terminate this Agreement by providing written notice thereof to the other Party. 2.5 Termination ??? Material Breach (a) Upon a breach, the non~breaching Party shall give written notice of such breach to the breaching Party. The breaching Party shall have ten (10) Calendar Days from receipt of the default notice within which to cure such breach; provided however, if such breach is not capable of cure within ten ( 1 0) Calendar Days, the breaching Party shall commence such cure within ten (l 0) Calendar Days after notice and continuously and diligently complete such cure within thirty (30) Calendar Days from receipt of the default notice; and, if cured within such time, the breach specified in such notice shall cease to exist. If a breach is not cured within the period provided for herein, the non-breaching Party shall have the right to terminate this Agreement by written notice. subject to the provisions of Sections 2.5(b) and (c) of this Agreement. (b) If the Party alleged to have breached disputes that breach has occurred or not been cured and neither Party alleges that reliable operations or compliance with Requirements as set forth in Section 1.6 of this Agreement are jeopardized, the dispute resolution provisions of Article 1 0 may be invoked and must be final prior to any notice of termination becoming effective. Regardless of whether the Party alleged to have breached disputes that breach has occurred or not been cured, if the Party alleging breach asserts that reliable operations or compliance with Requirements as set forth in Section 1.6 of this Agreement are jeopardized, the dispute resolution provisions of Article 1 0 may be invoked by one or both Parties but only for purposes of detennining the Parties' rights under the surviving provisions of this Agreement in accordance with Section 2.6 hereof, and any notice of termination shall be effective immediately, subject to the provisions of Section 2.5{ c) of this Agreement, and shall not be affected by such dispute. (c) Any notice of termination is subject to any required Regulatory Approvals. 2.6 Survival Upon termination or expiration of this Agreement for any reason, all obligations under this Agreement, except Inadvertent Interchange obligations incurred under this Agreement prior to termination or expiration, which have not been satisfied prior to termination or expiration, shall terminate upon termination or expiration of this Agreement; provided however, that in all events, the provisions of Articles 1, 2, 9, l 0, 11, 14 and I 6 shall survive termination or expiration of this Agreement, in each case, for the survival period stipulated in this Agreement or, in the absence of such stipulation, the longest period permitted by Applicable Law. ARTICLE3 GENERAL 3.1 Power Watch and NorthWestern Covenants The provisions of this Article 3 represent the covenants and agreements of both Power Watch and North Western. 3.2 GWA Balancing Authority Area and North Western Balancing Authority Area {a) Except as required by this Agreement and Requirements, Power Watch shaH retain the right to independently plan and operate the GWA Balancing Authority Area to meet its obligations and shall be or cause Glacier Wind 1 or Glacier Wind 2, respectively. to be responsible for the planning, construction, operation and maintenance of the Glacier Wind l and Glacier Wind 2 facilities for the term of this Agreement. Except as required by this Agreement and Requirements, North Western shaH retain the right to independently plan and direct the operation of the NorthWestern Balancing Authority Area to meet its obligations. (b) Power Watch and NorthWestern agree to maintain, or cause to be maintained, the facilities of the GWA Balancing Authority Area and the NorthWestern System respectively, in accordance with Requirements to the extent necessary to perform their respective obligations under this Agreement; provided that nothing in this Agreement requires NorthWestern to maintain any particular path, OTC or other rating of its Transmission System or to, in any respect, maintain any other Transmission System. ??? 3.3 Points of lntereonnedion; Interconnection Facilities This Agreement governs the coordinated operation by North Western and Power Watch of the Points of Interconnection between the GWA Balancing Authority Area and the NorthWestern Balancing Authority Area inclusive of the points set out and described in the NorthWestern Interconnection Agreements and the GW 2 LLC - Glacier Electric Interconnection Agreement. (a) Power Watch shall or shall cause the owners of Interconnection Facilities within the GWA Balancing Authority Area to be responsible for the operation and maintenance of such Interconnection Facilities. NorthWestern shall own and be responsible for the operation and maintenance of the Transmission Service Provider Interconnection Facilities as described in the NorthWestern Interconnection Agreements. (b) Subject to any Requirements, changes or additions to the Glacier Wind 1 Project Interconnection Facilities may only be made by agreement of GW 1 LLC and NorthWestern in writing. 3.4 Partidpation in the NWPP Reserve Sharing Program NorthWestern and Power Watch, and each of them, shall, during the operation of the GWA Balancing Authority Area, take all actions and meet all obligations necessary to participate in the NWPP Reserve Sharing Program. Power Watch shall continue these actions and maintain these obligations throughout the term of this Agreement to enable receipt and delivery of reserves as a participant of the NWPP Reserve Sharing Program, and shall operate in accordance with applicable NWPP and WECC Standards. ARTICLE4 INTERCONNECfED OPERATION 4.1 Covenants of Power Watch and NorthWestern The provisions of this Article 4 represent the covenants and agreements of Power Watch and North Western. 4.2 Maintain Interconnedions (a) The Points of Interconnection between the NorthWestern Balancing Authority Area and GWA Balancing Authority Area shall, from the time of initial Interconnection and, thereafter, at all times during the term of the Agreement thereafter, remain interconnected at the Points of Interconnection except: (i) subject to Article 12, during the occurrence of an event of Force Majeure which renders such a Party unable to remain interconnected~ (ii) during Forced Unavailability; (iii) during such period or under such circumstances that Requirements provide for or require the disconnection of such systems; (iv) during Planned Maintenance which has been scheduled in accordance with Section 4.6; and (v) during such other periods of time as Power Watch and NorthWestern members of the Joint Operating Committee (or such other person as may be designated in writing for such purpose) may agree pursuant to any applicable Operating Procedure. (b) Notwithstanding the foregoing: (i) the Points of Interconnection between the GW A Balancing Authority Area and the NorthWestern Balancing Authority Area shall not remain interconnected unless Power Watch and NorthWestern, and each of them, are both satisfied that such Interconnections will not jeopardize the safe and reliable operation of the NorthWestern Balancing Authority Area and the GW A Balancing Authority Area; (ii) the facilities of Power Watch within the GW A Balancing Authority Area and the NorthWestern Balancing Authority Area and the Interconnections between the North Western Balancing Authority Area and GWA Balancing Authority Area shall, from the time of initial Interconnections and, thereafter, at all times during the term of the Agreement thereafter, be operated in accordance with Requirements and all Coordinated Operating Procedures established from time to time pursuant to Article 8; and (iii) nothing in this Agreement shall abrogate or be interpreted as abrogating Power Watch's or NorthWestern's duties and responsibilities with respect to Requirements in respect of the safe and reliable operation of the GW A Balancing Authority Area and the NorthWestern Balancing Authority Area, respectively. 4.3 Balancing Authority Area Operations (a) Power Watch shall procure or otherwise provide Balancing Authority services for the GW A Balancing Authority Area. The postponing Party must limit the duration of any such postponement to the extent practicable in accordance with Good Utility Practice. 4. 7 Line Losses Interchange Schedules between the GWA Balancing Authority Area and the NorthWestern Balancing Authority Area will include line loss amoWlts for the NorthWestern System in accordance with the OA IT. 4.8 Tagging and OASIS Scheduling of energy across the Interconnections, including tagging and posting on OASIS, shall be in accordance with the OA TI and Requirements. 4.9 Notification of Unavailability In the event that either: (a) any Party's Interconnection Facilities are unavailable for use in accordance with the provisions of this Agreement, or the Interconnections are opened or derated, as a result of Forced Unavailability or Force Majeure or the other provisions of this Agreement; or (b) any Party otherwise is unable to meet one or more of the terms or conditions of this Agreement, the Party affected thereby or with knowledge thereof (the .. Affected Party") shall promptly provide the other Party (or a person designated by said Party) with notification of the circumstances of the unavailability, or opening or derating or failure and shall promptly provide the other Party (or a person designated by said Party) with notification of the details of such Force Majeure, Forced Unavailability or inability, as the case may be, setting forth: (i) a description of the event causing the Force Majeure, Forced Unavailability or inability to meet the tenns or conditions of this Agreement. as the case may be; (ii) a description of the actions it is taking or proposing to take to restore availability or close the Interconnections or restore the rating or meet the terms or conditions of this Agreement, as the case may be; and (iii) an estimate of the time at which the unavailability or failure to meet the terms or conditions of this Agreement, as the case may be. shall be corrected or the Interconnections will be closed or the rating restored, and update such notification as appropriate. record_data.record_plain_text: BHE POWER WATCH, LLC MARKET-BASED RATE TARIFF 1. Applicability: This Tariff is applicable to all wholesale sales of electric energy, capacity and ancillary services by BHE Power Watch, LLC (“Power Watch” or “Seller”) at market-based rates. 2. Availability: Power Watch makes electric energy and capacity available under this Tariff to any purchaser, except as prohibited below, with whom Power Watch has contracted. 3. Ancillary Services: Power Watch also will make available to any purchaser with whom it has contracted, the ancillary services listed in this Paragraph 3. PJM: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service, energy imbalance service, and operating reserve service (which includes spinning, 10-minute, and 30-minute reserves) for sale into the market administered by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. (“PJM”) and, where the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff permits, the self-supply of these services to purchasers for a bilateral sale that is used to satisfy the ancillary services requirements of the PJM Office of Interconnection. New York: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service, and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute non-synchronous, 30-minute operating reserves, 10-minute spinning reserves, and 10-minute non-spinning reserves) for sale to purchasers in the market administered by the New York Independent System Operator, Inc. New England: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service (automatic generator control), operating reserve service (which includes 10-minute spinning reserve, 10-minute non-spinning reserve, and 30-minute operating reserve service) to purchasers within the markets administered by ISO New England, Inc. California: Seller offers regulation service, spinning reserve service, and non-spinning reserve service to the California Independent System Operator Corporation (“CAISO”) and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to the CAISO. MISO: Seller offers regulation service and operating reserve service (which includes 10-minute spinning reserve and 10-minute supplemental reserve) for sale to the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. (“MISO”) and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to MISO. Southwest Power Pool: Seller offers regulation service and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute spinning reserve and 10-minute supplemental reserve) for sale to the Southwest Power Pool, Inc. (“SPP”) and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to SPP. Third-party ancillary services: Seller offers Regulation Service, Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service, Energy and Generator Imbalance Service, Operating Reserve-Spinning, Operating Reserve Supplemental, and Primary Frequency Response Service. Sales will not include the following: (1) sales to an RTO or an ISO, i.e., where that entity has no ability to self-supply ancillary services but instead depends on third parties; and (2) sales to a traditional, franchised public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier, or sales where the underlying transmission service is on the system of the public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier. Sales of Operating Reserve-Spinning and Operating Reserve-Supplemental will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff (“OATT”) requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except where the Commission has granted authorization. Sales of Regulation Service and Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own OATT requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except at rates not to exceed the buying public utility transmission provider’s OATT rate for the same service or where the Commission has granted authorization. 4. Rates: All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and Power Watch. 5. Other Terms and Conditions: All other terms and conditions shall be established by agreement between the purchaser and Power Watch. 6. Compliance with Commission Regulations: Power Watch shall comply with the provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning Power Watch’s market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes Power Watch to engage in affiliate sales under this Tariff or otherwise restricts or limits Power Watch’s market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning Power Watch’s market-based rate authority will constitute a violation of this Tariff. 7. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority: (a) Power Watch does not have authority under this tariff to make sales within the Nevada Power Company, PacifiCorp-East, or PacifiCorp-West balancing authority areas. See Sierra Pacific Power Co., 95 FERC ¶ 61,193, at 61,675, reh’g dismissed, 96 FERC ¶ 61,050 (2001); see also Sierra Pacific Power Co., 111 FERC ¶ 61,259, at P 21 (2005); Nevada Power Co., 155 FERC ¶ 61,249, at P 3 (2016); NaturEner Glacier 1 Wind Energy, LLC, Docket Nos. ER11-4666-005, et al. (Nov. 2, 2022); Nev. Power Co., 189 FERC ¶ 61,225 (2024); AlbertaEx, L.P., et al., Docket Nos. ER25-335-000, et al. (Dec. 31, 2024). (b) Sales of energy and capacity are permissible under this tariff in all balancing authority areas where Power Watch has been granted market-based rate authority. Sales of energy and capacity under this tariff are also permissible at the metered boundary between Power Watch’s mitigated balancing authority area and a balancing authority area where Power Watch has been granted market-based rate authority provided: (i) legal title of the power sold transfers at the metered boundary of the balancing authority area where Power Watch has market-based rate authority; and (ii) if Power Watch sells at the metered boundary of a mitigated balancing authority area at market-based rates, then neither it nor its affiliates can sell into that mitigated balancing authority area from the outside. Power Watch must retain, for a period of five years from the date of the sale, all data and information related to the sale that demonstrates compliance with items (i) and (ii) above. (c) In Docket No. ER09-1184-000, Power Watch received waiver of: Subparts B and C of Part 35, except for sections 35.12 (a), 35.13(b), 35.15 and 35.16; Part 41, Part 101, and Part 141, except section 141.15; and received blanket approval under Part 34. 8. Seller Category: Power Watch is a Category 2 Seller in the Northwest, Northeast, Central, Southwest, and Southwest Power Pool regions and a Category 1 Seller in the Southeast region, as defined in 18 C.F.R § 35.36(a). 9. Revisions to Tariff: Power Watch may file revisions to this Tariff with the Commission. Nothing contained in this Tariff shall be construed as affecting or limiting in any way the right of Power Watch to unilaterally file with the Commission for a change in any aspect of this Tariff under Section 205 of the Federal Power Act pursuant to the Commission’s Rules and Regulations promulgated thereunder. 10. Effective Date: This Tariff is effective on the date specified by the Commission.
